objectives:

    This course enables the students to better appreciate the law governing special contracts like, indemnity, guarantee, agency, etc. which are more relevant in the contemporary society. Law contained in several legislations apart from the Indian Contract Act is taught in this Course.

unit 1:
    Contract of Indemnity –Definition, Nature and Scope - Rights of indemnity holder – Commencement of the indemnifier's liability – Contract of Guarantee – Definition, Nature and Scope – Difference between contract of indemnity and Guarantee – Rights of surety – Discharge of Surety – Extent of Surety's liability – Co-surety.

unit 2:
    Contract of Bailment – Definition – Kinds – Rights and Duties of Bailor and Bailee – Rights of Finder of goods as Bailee – Contract of pledge – Definition – Comparison with Bailment – Rights and duties of Pawnor and Pawnee

unit 3:
    Agency – Definition – Creation of Agency – Kinds of Agents – Distinction between Agent and Servant – Rights and Duties of Agent – Relation of Principal with third parties – Delegation – Duties and Rights of Agent – Extent of Agents authority – Personal liability of Agent – Termination of Agency.

unit 4:
    Indian Partnership Act – Definition – Nature, Mode of determining the existence of Partnership – Relation of Partner to one another – Rights and duties of partner – Relation of partners with third parties – Types of partners – Admission– Retirement, and Expulsion of partners Dissolution of Firm – Registration of Firms.

unit 5:
    Sale of Goods Act – The Contract of sale – Agreement to sell - Conditions and Warranties – Passing of property – Transfer of title – Performance of the Contract – Rights of Unpaid Seller – Remedies for Breach of Contract.


books prescribed:
    Singh, Avtar, Law of Contract and Specific Relief, 11th Edition, (Lucknow: Eastern Book Company, 2013)

questions:

    Unit 1 - Contract of Indemnity and Guarantee

        Define Contract of Indemnity and explain its nature and scope. Discuss the rights of indemnity holder and commencement of the indemnifier's liability with relevant case laws.

        Explain the concept of Contract of Guarantee. Distinguish between contract of indemnity and contract of guarantee. Discuss the rights of surety and discharge of surety with leading judicial pronouncements.

        Critically analyse the extent of surety's liability under the Contract of Guarantee. Examine the concept of co-surety and the liability of co-sureties with relevant case laws.

    Unit 2 - Contract of Bailment and Pledge

        Define Bailment and explain different kinds of bailment. Discuss the rights and duties of Bailor and Bailee with relevant judicial interpretations.

        Examine the rights of finder of goods as bailee. Critically analyse the provisions relating to contract of bailment with leading case laws.

        Define Contract of Pledge and distinguish it from bailment. Discuss the rights and duties of Pawnor and Pawnee with relevant judicial pronouncements.

    Unit 3 - Law of Agency

        Explain the concept of Agency. Discuss the creation of agency and different kinds of agents. Distinguish between agent and servant with relevant case laws.

        Critically examine the rights and duties of agent. Discuss the relation of principal with third parties and the extent of agent's authority with leading judicial interpretations.

        Discuss the concept of delegation in agency. Examine the personal liability of agent and termination of agency with relevant case laws.

    Unit 4 - Indian Partnership Act

        Define Partnership under the Indian Partnership Act. Discuss the nature and mode of determining the existence of partnership with relevant judicial pronouncements.

        Examine the relation of partner to one another and rights and duties of partners. Discuss the relation of partners with third parties and types of partners with leading case laws.

        Critically analyse the provisions relating to admission, retirement and expulsion of partners. Discuss dissolution of firm and registration of firms with relevant judicial interpretations.

    Unit 5 - Sale of Goods Act

        Distinguish between contract of sale and agreement to sell under the Sale of Goods Act. Explain the difference between conditions and warranties with relevant case laws.

        Examine the provisions relating to passing of property and transfer of title under the Sale of Goods Act. Discuss performance of the contract with leading judicial pronouncements.

        Discuss the rights of unpaid seller under the Sale of Goods Act. Examine the remedies available for breach of contract with relevant case laws.
